ought, an Eça increasingly distant from the French cultural model which had marked his education. Teresa Pinto Coelho is Full Professor and Chair in Anglo-Portuguese Studies at the Universidade Nova de Lisboa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPeriodicalsxPublishingxHistoryy19th century. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aModern Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aAnglophile.  aCultural Influence.  aEnglish Thought.  aEça de Queirós.  aFrench Cultural Model.  aLiterary Influence.  aLiterary Studies.  aParis.  aPortuguese Literature.  aVictorian Era.  aVictorian Press.  aVictorian Publications.1 aEarle, T. F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782042044423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782042044/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles